-- Convio, Energen, ITT, Westwood Holdings: U.S. Equity Preview
-- B y   W h i t n e y   K i s l i n g
-- 2012-02-10T22:49:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-10/convio-energen-itt-westwood-holdings-group-u-s-equity-market-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in U.S. trading on Feb. 13. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of 5 p.m. in New York.  Convio Inc. (CNVO)   gained 0.2 percent to $15.82. Gabelli
& Co. reported a new stake in the Austin, Texas-based provider
of software for non-profit organizations equal to 7.8 percent.  Energen Corp. (EGN)  : The Birmingham, Alabama-based oil
and natural gas company said it is buying a proved undeveloped
Wolfberry package for $68.55 million.  ITT Corp. (ITT US): The manufacturer rescheduled its 2011
results to Feb. 29 so that it can review spinoff data because of
“complexities” on the financial information. The company also
will give its 2012 forecast that day.  Westwood Holdings Group Inc. (WHG)   rose 1 percent to
$39.90. The Dallas-based investment advisory company named Mark
Freeman its chief investment officer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Whitney Kisling in  New York  at 
 wkisling@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 